{
  "texts": [
    "Positive results are more likely to be published than negative or inconclusive results.",
    "This bias can lead to an overrepresentation of certain findings, which can skew the domain knowledge.",
    "Studies with small sample sizes, which are not representative of a larger population, may contain results that are unreliable or not generalizable.",
    "Additionally, even though our entity labelling schema aims to identify the controlling ($GEN-E_AGENT#) and child ($GENE_TARGET#) entities in a relationship, not all sentences clearly indicate the direction of the interaction.",
    "In such cases, information about known controlling entities, such as regulatory genes or transcriptional factors, in the target network can help identify the direction of the relation."
  ]
}